# CHECKPOINTS — {{.Project}}

> Objective checks any reviewer (human or AI) uses to decide if the
> repository is in a healthy end-state. In multi-agent systems we don't
> evaluate the path, we evaluate the destination.

## C1 — Harness is complete

- [ ] `AGENTS.md`, `init.sh`, `feature_list.json`, `progress/current.md` exist.
- [ ] `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/conventions.md`, `docs/verification.md` exist.
- [ ] `./init.sh` exits with code 0.

## C2 — State is coherent

- [ ] At most one feature is `in_progress` in `feature_list.json`.
- [ ] Every `done` feature has tests that pass.
- [ ] `progress/current.md` is empty OR describes the active session
      (no leftover noise from prior sessions).

## C3 — Code respects the architecture

- [ ] The source tree only contains the modules listed in `docs/architecture.md`.
- [ ] No accidental dependencies introduced (read `docs/conventions.md`).
- [ ] No `print()` / `console.log` left over for debug; no orphan TODOs.

## C4 — Verification is real

- [ ] The test suite has at least one test per module under change.
- [ ] Tests use real temp filesystems where applicable (no fs mocks).
- [ ] Running the test command shows > 0 tests and all green.

## C5 — The session closed cleanly

- [ ] No suspicious untracked files (`*.tmp`, build artefacts not in `.gitignore`).
- [ ] `progress/history.md` carries one entry for the most recent session.
- [ ] The feature you worked on is in its correct final status.
{{if .SDDMode}}
## C6 — Spec-driven contract upheld

> Only applies when `rules.require_approved_spec_to_implement` is set
> in `feature_list.json`. The reviewer skips C6 for non-SDD features.

- [ ] Every feature with `sdd: true` past `pending` has all three files
      under `specs/<feature.name>/`: `requirements.md`, `design.md`,
      `tasks.md`.
- [ ] `requirements.md` uses EARS notation (WHEN / WHILE / WHERE /
      IF…THEN) and every `acceptance` bullet from `feature_list.json`
      maps to ≥ 1 R-id in the traceability table.
- [ ] `design.md` lists every file the implementer touched, plus at
      least one rejected alternative.
- [ ] Every `T<n>` in `tasks.md` is checked `[x]` and references the
      R-id(s) it covers.
- [ ] `korva harness check` exits 0 (or `vault_harness_check` returns
      `ok: true` over MCP).
{{end}}
---

**How to use this file:** a reviewer agent (see `.claude/agents/reviewer.md`)
walks each checkbox, marks `[x]` or `[ ]`, and rejects the session close
when any C1-C5{{if .SDDMode}}/C6{{end}} box is empty.
